msgstr ""
"Levanta um :ref:`evento de auditoria <auditing>` ``os.walk`` com os "
"argumentos ``top``, ``topdown``, ``onerror`` e ``followlinks``."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3730
msgid ""
"This function now calls :func:`os.scandir` instead of :func:`os.listdir`, "
"making it faster by reducing the number of calls to :func:`os.stat`."
msgstr ""
"Esta funĂ§ĂŁo agora chama :func:`os.scandir` em vez de :func:`os.listdir`, "
"tornando-a mais rĂĄpida reduzindo o nĂşmero de chamadas a :func:`os.stat`."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3744
msgid ""
"This behaves exactly like :func:`walk`, except that it yields a 4-tuple "
"``(dirpath, dirnames, filenames, dirfd)``, and it supports ``dir_fd``."
msgstr ""
"Se comporta exatamente como :func:`walk`, exceto que produz um tupla de 4 "
"elementos ``(dirpath, dirnames, filenames, dirfd)``, e tem suporte a "
"``dir_fd``."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3747
msgid ""
"*dirpath*, *dirnames* and *filenames* are identical to :func:`walk` output, "
"and *dirfd* is a file descriptor referring to the directory *dirpath*."
msgstr ""
"*dirpath*, *dirnames* e *filenames* sĂŁo idĂŞnticos Ă  saĂ­da de :func:`walk` e "
"*dirfd* ĂŠ um descritor de arquivo que faz referĂŞncia ao diretĂłrio *dirpath*."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3750
msgid ""
"This function always supports :ref:`paths relative to directory descriptors "
"<dir_fd>` and :ref:`not following symlinks <follow_symlinks>`.  Note however "
"that, unlike other functions, the :func:`fwalk` default value for "
"*follow_symlinks* is ``False``."
msgstr ""
"Esta funĂ§ĂŁo sempre tem suporte a :ref:`caminhos relativos aos descritores de "
"diretĂłrio <dir_fd>` e :ref:`nĂŁo seguir links simbĂłlicos <follow_symlinks>`. "
"Observe, entretanto, que, ao contrĂĄrio de outras funĂ§Ăľes, o valor padrĂŁo :"
"func:`fwalk` para *follow_symlinks* ĂŠ ``False``."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3757
msgid ""
"Since :func:`fwalk` yields file descriptors, those are only valid until the "
"next iteration step, so you should duplicate them (e.g. with :func:`dup`) if "
"you want to keep them longer."
msgstr ""
"Uma vez que :func:`fwalk` produz descritores de arquivo, eles sĂł sĂŁo vĂĄlidos "
"atĂŠ a prĂłxima etapa de iteraĂ§ĂŁo, entĂŁo vocĂŞ deve duplicĂĄ-los (por exemplo, "
"com :func:`dup`) se quiser mantĂŞ-los por mais tempo."

#: ../../library/os.rst:3765
msgid ""
"import os\n"
"for root, dirs, files, rootfd in os.fwalk('python/Lib/xml'):\n"
"    print(root, \"consumes\", end=\" \")\n"
"    print(sum([os.stat(name, dir_fd=rootfd).st_size for name in files]),\n"
"          end=\" \")\n"
"    print(\"bytes in\", len(files), \"non-directory files\")\n"
"    if '__pycache__' in dirs:\n"
"        dirs.remove('__pycache__')  # don't visit __pycache__ directories"
msgstr ""
"import os\n"
"for root, dirs, files, rootfd in os.fwalk('python/Lib/xml'):\n"
"    print(root, \"consome\", end=\" \")\n"
"    print(sum([os.stat(name, dir_fd=rootfd).st_size for name in files]),\n"
"          end=\" \")\n"
"    print(\"bytes em\", len(files), \"arquivos que nĂŁo sĂŁo diretĂłrios\")\n"
"    if '__pycache__' in dirs:\n"
"        dirs.remove('__pycache__')  # nĂŁo visita diretĂłrios de __pycache__"

#: ../../library/os.rst:3774
msgid ""
"In the next example, walking the tree bottom-up is essential: :func:`rmdir` "
"doesn't allow deleting a directory before the directory is empty::"
msgstr ""
"No prĂłximo exemplo, percorrer a ĂĄrvore de baixo para cima ĂŠ essencial: :func:"
"`rmdir` nĂŁo permite excluir um diretĂłrio antes que o diretĂłrio esteja vazio::"

#: ../../library/os.rst:3778
msgid ""
"# Delete everything reachable from the directory named in \"top\",\n"
"# assuming there are no symbolic links.\n"
"# CAUTION:  This is dangerous!  For example, if top == '/', it\n"
"# could delete all your disk files.\n"
"import os\n"
"for root, dirs, files, rootfd in os.fwalk(top, topdown=False):\n"
"    for name in files:\n"
"        os.unlink(name, dir_fd=rootfd)\n"
"    for name in dirs:\n"
"        os.rmdir(name, dir_fd=rootfd)"
msgstr ""
"# Exclui tudo que for acessĂ­vel do diretĂłrio nomeado em \"top\",\n"
"# presumindo que nĂŁo hĂĄ links simbĂłlicos.\n"
"# CUIDADO: Isso ĂŠ perigoso! Por exemplo, se top == '/',\n"
"# ele pode excluir todos os seus arquivos de disco.\n"
"import os\n"
"for root, dirs, files, rootfd in os.fwalk(top, topdown=False):\n"
"    for name in files:\n"
"        os.unlink(name, dir_fd=rootfd)\n"
"    for name in dirs:\n"
"        os.rmdir(name, dir_fd=rootfd)"

#: ../../library/os.rst:3789
msgid ""
"Raises an :ref:`auditing event <auditing>` ``os.fwalk`` with arguments "
"``top``, ``topdown``, ``onerror``, ``follow_symlinks``, ``dir_fd``."
msgstr ""
"Levanta um :ref:`evento de auditoria <auditing>` ``os.fwalk`` com os "
